Total: 40 cards + 3 magi   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Strategy? Heh.<br>
<br>
Start with Gogar. Hope to draw a thermal blast,<br>
ground breaker, or greater vaal, and you just<br>
might finish off the opposing magi if you go<br>
second.<br>
<br>
Grega picks up where Gogar left off.<br>
<br>
Emec goes last for greater odds of getting the<br>
relics. He uses his power with the relics<br>
well. Hammer on your turn, slingshot on the<br>
opponents turn.<br>
<br>
Grow and cragnoc provide you with extra<br>
energy. Thermal blast, ground breaker, drakan,<br>
and greater vaal deal death in spots, while<br>
typhoon, xyx elder, and ballistic balder rain<br>
mass destruction on the opposing army. Fate&#39;s<br>
whimsey and loaded dice help when those snake<br>
eyes rear their ugly head.<br>
<br>
Not meant for real competition, but loads of<br>
fun if you like rolling dice. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
